ies, with uncertainty that reflects both aleatoric noise and epistemic gaps due to topological rarity. Applications include personalized organ motion prediction in image-guided surgery, detection of early-stage morphological anomalies, and synthetic data augmentation for rare disease modeling. By dynamically aligning latent geometries and adapting probabilistic priors to local structure, our method surpasses static frameworks in generalization, calibration, and interpretability.",
